<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="25" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,692,717]" pageId="25" pageNumber="520">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[323,501,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,501,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="520">A. colombiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[509,600,692,717]" pageId="25" pageNumber="520" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[509,600,692,717]" pageId="25" pageNumber="520">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be readily recognized by conspicous external features, which include the overall coloration, the shape of the head, and the outline of dorsum. Although these features are useful to distinguish this species from the morphologically similar 
<taxonomicName box="[821,1035,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboferrugineus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[821,1035,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="520">A. alboferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1046,1139,764,789]" pageId="25" pageNumber="520" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1046,1139,764,789]" pageId="25" pageNumber="520">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, their male genitalia also differ in several respects. In the male of 
<taxonomicName box="[630,810,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[630,810,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="520">A. colombiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[821,914,799,824]" pageId="25" pageNumber="520" rank="species">
